    • Method Detail

      • getDays

        java.lang.String getDays()
        Get the list of named days for a WEEKLY calendar period. Day ranges are separated by hyphens (e.g. Su-Sa). Use two-letter day constants SUNDAY, MONDAY, TUESDAY, WEDNESDAY, THURSDAY, FRIDAY, and SATURDAY. A week starts on SUNDAY, ends on SATURDAY.
        Returns:
        the list of named days for a WEEKLY calendar period

      • getMonths

        java.lang.String getMonths()
        Get the list of named months for a MONTHLY calendar period. Month ranges are separated by hyphens (e.g. Jan-Dec). Use three-letter month constants JANUARY, FEBRUARY, MARCH, APRIL, MAY, JUNE, JULY, AUGUST, SEPTEMBER, OCTOBER, NOVEMBER, and DECEMBER.
        Returns:
        the list of named months for a MONTHLY calendar period

      • listTimes

        java.util.List<ISchedule.Item.Calendar.Time> listTimes()
        Get the list of run times for this calendar's scheduled days. More than one run time can exist in a calendar as long as the run times do not overlap
        Returns:
        the list of run times for this calendar's scheduled days

      • getDaysOfMonth

        java.lang.String getDaysOfMonth()
        Get the set of numbered days for a MONTHLY calendar period. The scheduled days for a MONTHLY calendar period can be either a set of numbered days separated by commas and hyphens (e.g. 1-5,10-20) or a recurring named day (e.g. Every Monday)
        Returns:
        the set of days or recurring named day for a MONTHLY calendar period

      • getRecurrence

        java.lang.String getRecurrence()
        Get the recurring day setting for a MONTHLY calendar period. The scheduled days for a MONTHLY calendar period can be either a set of numbered days separated by commas and hyphens (e.g. 1-5,10-20) or a recurring named day (e.g. Every Monday). If there is a recurrent day setting but no named day, then simply "day" is assumed.
        Returns:
        EVERY, FIRST, SECOND, THIRD, FOURTH, LAST or null

      • getRecurrentDay

        java.lang.String getRecurrentDay()
        Get the recurrent named day setting for a MONTHLY calendar period. The scheduled days for a MONTHLY calendar period can be either a set of numbered days separated by commas and hyphens (e.g. 1-5,10-20) or a recurring named day (e.g. Every Monday). If there is a recurrent day setting but no named day, then simply "day" is assumed.
        Returns:
        SUNDAY, MONDAY, TUESDAY, WEDNESDAY, THURSDAY, FRIDAY, SATURDAY, or null

      • setDaysOfMonth

        void setDaysOfMonth(java.lang.String daysOfMonth)
        Set the set of numbered days for a MONTHLY calendar period. The scheduled days for a MONTHLY calendar period can be either a set of numbered days separated by commas and hyphens (e.g. 1-5,10-20) or a recurring named day (e.g. Every Monday)
        Parameters:

      • setDaysOfMonth

        void setDaysOfMonth(java.lang.String recurrence,
                    java.lang.String day)
        Set the recurrence and named day for a MONTHLY calendar period. The scheduled days for a MONTHLY calendar period can be either a set of numbered days separated by commas and hyphens (e.g. 1-5,10-20) or a recurring named day (e.g. Every Monday) If there is an recurrent day setting but no named day, then simply "day" is assumed.
        Parameters:
        recurrence - EVERY, FIRST, SECOND, THIRD, FOURTH, or LAST
        day - SUNDAY, MONDAY, TUESDAY, WEDNESDAY, THURSDAY, FRIDAY, SATURDAY, or null

      • isRecurrent

        boolean isRecurrent()
        Indicates whether there is a recurrent day setting for a MONTHLY calendar period. The scheduled days for a MONTHLY calendar period can be either a set of numbered days separated by commas and hyphens (e.g. 1-5,10-20) or a recurring named day (e.g. Every Monday). If there is an recurrent day setting but no named day, then simply "day" is assumed.
        Returns:
        true if there is an recurrent day setting; false otherwise
